{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: allergy-intolerance-eu-core_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH AllergyIntolerance instance conforming to the
    AllergyIntoleranceEuCore profile. Each invocation represents either a
    known allergy or intolerance, or a sentinel "no known allergies" record
    when no allergy data is available.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: AllergyIntoleranceEuCore
    Must-support elements covered (Mode B):
      code (SNOMED + preferred text), clinicalStatus, verificationStatus,
      type, category, patient, onsetDateTime (or absent-reason),
      reaction[].manifestation, reaction[].severity

  TWO-MODE PATTERN — `is empty` TEST
    The top-level branch tests `{% if allergyintolerance is empty %}`.
    Note: `is empty` (not `is null`) — triggers for null, empty string,
    and empty array alike. Callers may pass any of these to trigger Mode A.

  MODE A — NO KNOWN ALLERGY/INTOLERANCE (allergyintolerance is empty)

    ⚠ BUG — MISSING NARRATIVE: Mode A emits no `* text.status` or
    `* text.div` rule. The sentinel FSH instance therefore lacks the required
    FHIR narrative element, which will cause FHIR validator warnings. The
    `text.status = #generated` and `text.div` block that follows the sections
    loop is inside the `{% else %}` branch (Mode B only). Fix: add a
    `text.status = #generated` and minimal `text.div` to Mode A.

    A sentinel FSH instance is emitted carrying:
      code.coding[0]       = $sct#716186003 "No known allergy (situation)"
      onsetDateTime        → data-absent-reason #unknown
      clinicalStatus       = $allergyintolerance-clinical#active
      verificationStatus   = $allergyintolerance-verification#confirmed
    The sentinel `clinicalStatus` is set to #active even though no allergy
    exists — this satisfies the profile's cardinality requirement for the
    status element.
    A single HTML cell "No known allergies or intolerances" is emitted.
    No HEAD row is produced (see "HEAD bag placement" below).

  MODE B — ALLERGY/INTOLERANCE DATA PRESENT

    HEAD BAG PLACEMENT — INSIDE {% else %} ONLY
      Unlike most templates where HEAD calls are unconditional, all
      `addHEAD_th()` calls in this template sit inside the `{% else %}`
      branch. This means:
        Mode A → HEAD bag empty → %%HEAD%% section is empty string
        Mode B → 5-column HEAD row populated
      When Mode A is rendered, callers consuming %%HEAD%% will receive an
      empty string. External table renderers must handle this gracefully.

    FIVE-COLUMN HTML TABLE (Mode B only):
      Column 1 — Allergy/Intolerance name (preferred term or display)
      Column 2 — Onset date (pill badge or "?")
      Column 3 — Clinical status ("active" / "inactive")
      Column 4 — Category (allergy category code or "?")
      Column 5 — Reaction(s) combined display

    SNOMED CODING — CONDITIONAL [+]
      The SNOMED code is emitted only when `allergyintolerance.snomed.code`
      is non-empty, using `coding[+]` (append, not explicit [0]):
        * code.coding[+] = $sct#...
      This means a second coding could theoretically be added by subsequent
      rules; the [+] form leaves the slice open.

    CODE TEXT / TD 1 — PREFERRED TERM OR DISPLAY
      Both the FSH `code.text` and HTML td 1 use the same two-branch logic:
        preferredTerm (if non-empty) → used in both FSH and HTML
        snomed.display (fallback)    → used in both FSH and HTML
      Unlike some other templates, there is no additional check that
      preferredTerm differs from display before using it.

    CLINICAL STATUS — DERIVED FROM END DATE
      Rather than reading an explicit status field, clinical activity is
      inferred from the presence or absence of an end date:
        end is empty   → clinicalStatus = #active
        end is present → clinicalStatus = #inactive
      This is a heuristic — an ended allergy is assumed resolved/inactive.

    VERIFICATION STATUS — ALWAYS CONFIRMED
      `* verificationStatus.coding = $allergyintolerance-verification#confirmed`
      is emitted unconditionally for all Mode B instances. The sentinel (Mode A)
      also carries `#confirmed`.

    TYPE AND CATEGORY — RAW CODE VALUES
      Both use the FSH short code form with a `#` prefix embedded in the template:
        * type     = #{{ allergyintolerance.type }}
        * category = #{{ allergyintolerance.category }}
      The caller supplies the raw code value without `#`; the template adds it.

    REACTIONS — TWO FIXED SLOTS
      Up to two reactions are supported via separate `reaction1` and `reaction2`
      object fields (not an array). Each is individually conditional on its
      `.code` field:
        reaction[+].manifestation.coding[0] = $sct#code "display"
        reaction[=].severity = #severity
      The `| lower` filter normalises the severity value to lower-case
      regardless of how the caller supplies it (e.g. "Mild" → "mild").

    REACTION HTML SEPARATOR — ENTITY-ENCODED `<br>`
      When both reactions are present, the HTML td 5 combines their display
      strings with:
        `&lt;br> &lt;/br>`
      These are HTML entity references. In the rendered XHTML the entities
      will display as literal text `<br> </br>` rather than producing a
      visual line break. To produce an actual line break in the table cell,
      use `<br/>` (unencoded) instead. This appears to be an unintended
      encoding.

    NARRATIVE — FULL HEADED TABLE (Pattern 2, Mode B only)
      Both emitHEAD() and emitHTML() are flushed inside text.div — a complete
      table with header row in the inline narrative. Mode A has no narrative
      at all (see bug note above).

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                                 │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├──────────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                               │ string   │ Unique resource id.                        │
  │ patient.instanceid                       │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.              │
  │ patient.name                             │ string   │ Full display name for the patient Ref.     │
  │ allergyintolerance                       │ object?  │ Empty/null → Mode A. Non-empty → Mode B.  │
  │   .snomed.code                           │ string?  │   SNOMED CT code (conditional).            │
  │   .snomed.display                        │ string   │   SNOMED display text.                     │
  │   .preferredTerm                         │ string?  │   Preferred display override for code.text │
  │                                          │          │   and HTML td 1. Used unconditionally when │
  │                                          │          │   non-empty.                               │
  │   .start                                 │ string?  │   ISO 8601 onset date. When empty,        │
  │                                          │          │   data-absent-reason emitted.              │
  │   .end                                   │ string?  │   ISO 8601 abatement date. Presence        │
  │                                          │          │   determines clinicalStatus (#active /     │
  │                                          │          │   #inactive).                              │
  │   .type                                  │ string?  │   FHIR AllergyIntolerance type code        │
  │                                          │          │   (e.g. "allergy", "intolerance").         │
  │                                          │          │   Template adds `#` prefix.                │
  │   .category                              │ string?  │   FHIR category code (e.g. "food",         │
  │                                          │          │   "medication"). Template adds `#` prefix. │
  │   .reaction1                             │ object?  │   First reaction (optional).               │
  │     .code                                │ string   │     SNOMED CT code.                        │
  │     .display                             │ string   │     Reaction display text.                 │
  │     .severity                            │ string?  │     Severity code; | lower applied.        │
  │   .reaction2                             │ object?  │     Second reaction (optional; same        │
  │                                          │          │     structure as reaction1).               │
  └──────────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $sct                              — SNOMED CT; sentinel code 716186003, condition codes
    $allergyintolerance-clinical      — #active, #inactive
    $allergyintolerance-verification  — #confirmed

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-10-22
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-AllergyIntolerance-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: AllergyIntoleranceEuCore
Title: "AllergyIntolerance"
Description: "AllergyIntolerance"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{% if allergyintolerance is empty %}
{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE A — NO KNOWN ALLERGY/INTOLERANCE
  `is empty` catches null, empty string, and empty array.
  Emits a SNOMED sentinel code and data-absent-reason on onsetDateTime.
  clinicalStatus is set to #active to satisfy profile cardinality.
  ⚠ No text.status / text.div is emitted here — the narrative is missing.
    Add text.status = #generated and a text.div to correct this.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
* code.coding[0] = $sct#716186003 "No known allergy (situation)"
* patient = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"
* onsetDateTime.extension.url = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* onsetDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{# clinicalStatus #active required by profile even for a "no known allergy" sentinel #}
* clinicalStatus.coding = $allergyintolerance-clinical#active
* verificationStatus = $allergyintolerance-verification#confirmed
{# Single HTML cell — no table structure or HEAD row for the sentinel #}
{{ addHTML_tr() }}
{{ addHTML_td("No known allergies or intolerances") }}
{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{% else %}
{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  MODE B — ALLERGY/INTOLERANCE DATA PRESENT
  HEAD bag calls are HERE inside {% else %} — not unconditional.
  Mode A therefore produces an empty HEAD bag (no HEAD row emitted at all).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}

{# Five-column HEAD row — only populated when allergyintolerance is non-empty #}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Allergy/Intolerance") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Onset Date") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Status") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Type") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reaction") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── SNOMED code (conditional) ───────────────────────────────────────────────
  [+] append used — leaves room for additional codings if needed.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.snomed.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[+] = $sct#{{ allergyintolerance.snomed.code }} "{{ allergyintolerance.snomed.display }}"
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 1: allergy/intolerance name ─────────────────────────────────────────
  preferredTerm used unconditionally when non-empty (no further diff-check).
  Same value used for both FSH code.text and HTML td 1.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.preferredTerm is not empty %}
* code.text = "{{ allergyintolerance.preferredTerm }}"
{{ addHTML_td(allergyintolerance.preferredTerm) }}
{% else %}
* code.text = "{{ allergyintolerance.snomed.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(allergyintolerance.snomed.display) }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 2: onset date ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Present: onsetDateTime + pill badge.
  Absent: data-absent-reason extension + "?" cell.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.start is not empty %}
* onsetDateTime = "{{ allergyintolerance.start }}"
{{ addHTML_tdnb(allergyintolerance.start) }}
{% else %}
* onsetDateTime.extension.url = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* onsetDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{{ addHTML_td("?") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 3: clinical status — inferred from end date ──────────────────────────
  No explicit status field: active = no end date; inactive = end date present.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.end is empty %}
* clinicalStatus.coding = $allergyintolerance-clinical#active
{{ addHTML_td("active") }}
{% else %}
* clinicalStatus.coding = $allergyintolerance-clinical#inactive
{{ addHTML_td("inactive") }}
{% endif %}

{# verificationStatus always confirmed in Mode B #}
* verificationStatus.coding = $allergyintolerance-verification#confirmed

{#
  ── Type (FSH only) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Template adds `#` prefix; caller supplies the bare code value.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.type is not empty %}
* type = #{{ allergyintolerance.type }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 4: category ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Template adds `#` prefix; caller supplies the bare code value.
  "?" shown in HTML when category is absent; no FSH rule emitted.
#}
{% if allergyintolerance.category is not empty %}
* category = #{{ allergyintolerance.category }}
{{ addHTML_td(allergyintolerance.category) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("?") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── TD 5: reactions — two fixed slots ───────────────────────────────────────
  reaction1 and reaction2 are separate object fields (not an array). Each is
  individually conditional on its .code being non-empty.

  manifestation.coding[0] — explicit [0] on manifestation (one coding per reaction).
  severity — | lower filter normalises case (e.g. "Mild" → "mild").

  humantextreactions accumulates the HTML display string for td 5.
  Separator between reactions: `&lt;br> &lt;/br>` — HTML entity-encoded.
  ⚠ This renders as the literal text `<br> </br>` in the browser, not a
    visual line break. Use `<br/>` (unencoded) to produce an actual break.
#}
{% set humantextreactions = "" %}
{% if allergyintolerance.reaction1.code is not empty %}
* reaction[+].manifestation.coding[0] = $sct#{{ allergyintolerance.reaction1.code }} "{{ allergyintolerance.reaction1.display }}"
{% if allergyintolerance.reaction1.severity is not empty %}
* reaction[=].severity = #{{ allergyintolerance.reaction1.severity | lower }}
{% endif %}
{% set humantextreactions = allergyintolerance.reaction1.display %}
{% endif %}
{% if allergyintolerance.reaction2.code is not empty %}
* reaction[+].manifestation.coding[0] = $sct#{{ allergyintolerance.reaction2.code }} "{{ allergyintolerance.reaction2.display }}"
{% if allergyintolerance.reaction2.severity is not empty %}
* reaction[=].severity = #{{ allergyintolerance.reaction2.severity | lower }}
{% endif %}
{# ⚠ &lt;br> &lt;/br> encodes as literal text, not a visual line break #}
{% set humantextreactions = humantextreactions ~ "&lt;br> &lt;/br>" ~ allergyintolerance.reaction2.display %}
{% endif %}
{{ addHTML_td(humantextreactions) }}

{# Patient reference — placed after reaction blocks #}
* patient = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative — full headed table (Pattern 2) ──────────────────────────
  Both emitHEAD() and emitHTML() flushed. Mode A has no text.div at all
  (see bug note in file header).
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }} {{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

{% endif %} {# allergyintolerance is empty / not empty #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}
{# Mode A: HEAD bag empty — emits empty string. Mode B: 5-column HEAD row. #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
